                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5657: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-16T18:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>214. My 212, May 15, 5 p.m. Despite the President’s announcement, 11 of the 19
                    members of the Conservative directorate met yesterday, summoned by the
                    secretary, and began the work of passing upon the credentials of the delegates
                    to the Conservative Convention. This shows clearly that Chamorro controls the
                    majority of the directorate.</p>
                <pb facs="0600" n="490" xml:id="pg_490"/>
                <p>Cuadra Pasos stated definitely this morning that his faction will hold a separate
                    convention unless a compromise is reached before Sunday.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d416fn43">May 20.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
